@NODE "datasheet" "space_gc/datasheet (information)"


     NAME
        @{"space_gc" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/space_gc/MAIN"} -- a placeholder gadget class.

     SUPERCLASS
        gadgetclass

     REQUIRES
        bevel.image

     DESCRIPTION
        This class does more than just take up space. space.gadget allows you
        to create a GREL or layout resizable input areabox. You might render
        custom graphics in the area, for example, a icon editor graphic area
        might be based on space.gadget. This lets space.gadget handle its
        domain in a way compatible with not only the present layout, but any
        future custom layout domain methods. The application can handle rendering
        and clipping in this area on the application task. It presently sends
        notification of Mouse X/Y and the inner custom application rendering area
        of the space accounting for  any outer bevel (including preference bevel
        sizes changes).

     METHODS
        @{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63} -- Create the space gadget.  Passed to superclass.

        @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65} -- Set object attributes.  Passed to superclass first.

        @{"OM_DISPOSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 64} -- Passed to superclass.

        @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70} -- Set object notification attributes & render.
            Passed to superclass first.

        @{"OM_NOTIFY" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 69} -- Notify object attributes. Passed to superclass first.

        @{"GM_RENDER" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 302} -- Renders the gadget imagery.  Overrides the superclass.

        @{"GM_HITTEST" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 298} -- always returns @{"GMR_GADGETHIT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 368}, as long as the gadgets
            @{"GA_ReadOnly" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 189} attribute isn't set.

        @{"GM_GOACTIVE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 305} -- Passed to superclass first. Then sends mouseevent
            notification.

        @{"GM_HANDLEINPUT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 308} -- Handles input events once active.  Overrides the
            superclass. As long as the user keeps the mouse button pressed,
            the gadget sends notification events to its @{"ICA_TARGET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/icclass.h/File" 27}.

        @{"GM_GOINACTIVE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 311} -- Passed to superclass. A final notification is sent.

        @{"GM_DOMAIN" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/gadgetclass.h/File" 323} -- Calculates mix/max sizes. Overrides the superclass.


        All other methods are passed to the superclass.

